    "summary": "In 2012, Christian obtained a Bachelor of Science (HBO) degree in Life-Sciences and Diagnostics from Fontys University of Applied Sciences. Subsequently, he pursued a pre-master's program and successfully completed his Master's degree in Biomedical Sciences from Maastricht University in 2015. In parallel, he obtained a second Master's degree in Biomolecular Sciences from Toho University in Tokyo, Japan.\n\nIn 2015, Christian embarked on his PhD journey at the University Eye Clinic, Maastricht UMC+. His research focused on the development of a non-invasive ocular drug delivery system called the ocular coil. This project was undertaken within the framework of the Chemelot Institute for Science and Technology (InSciTe), in collaboration with Eyegle, and Eindhoven University of Technology (TU/e). In January 2020, he transitioned into a post-doctoral researcher role within the glaucoma team, specializing in the development and validation of innovative glaucoma implants. Additionally, he assumed the role of co-promotor for a PhD candidate in the field.\n\nIn 2023, Christian joined Brightlands Maastricht Health Campus as a Business Developer. In this capacity, he seized the opportunity to also focus on his own startup, Peyeoneer MedTech. His primary objective is to bring a novel glaucoma drainage implant to market through a first-in-man feasibility study and share the knowledge on how to do this with his peers.",
